Billecart-salmon Brut Champagne
The house of Billecart-salmon was founded in 818 in Maroun
Sur Ay near Epernay, in the heart of the Champagne region. This
cuvee is a blend of 35% Chardonnay, 35% Pinot Noir and 30%
Pinot Meunier grapes which come from the very best vineyards
In Marne.its orignt straw-colour is complemented by a steady
mousse of slowly rising bubbles. is nose is ofripe pears with a
delicate touch of cut hay. Billecart Salmon has an elegant fruits
flavour, leaving a clean fresh taste in the mouth
Paul Sapin Mâcon Lugny Cuvée Prestige 2005
Lugny is a small village in the Maconnais, Burgundy. The 2005
Paul sapin Macon Luany duvee Prestige 2005 disolays flora land
fruity aromas that give way to its lush, suave medium-bodied
character. It offers flavours reminiscent of lemon. dusted with
honey and minerals. This charming wine goes well with fish and
white meat dishes, and is also an excellent aperitif on its own.
Climbing Chardonnay 2005
The 2005 Climbing Chardonnay was made from the grapes
grown in Orange New South Wales. Australia.This cool climate
area produces elegant and fresh chardonnay, which offers
attractive flavours of citrus and nectarine fruits. The butters
notes from the rrench oak adds complexity to the wine, Unis is
a beautiful wine with a long finish. It goes perfectly well with
seatood dishes
Kirrihill Companions Clare Valley Shiraz 2004
This rich wine, from Clare Valley, South Australia, has intense
aromas of ripe mulberry and nutmeg, combined with vanilla oak
It is balanced and generous with sweet berry fruit and chocolate
notes, while the tannin adds to deliver a powertu wine that
lingers nicely on the palate. Enioy this favoursome wine with
red meat dishes
